# Regressions — Loom-scoped, append-only.
# Contract: protocols/regressions.schema.toon
# Consumers: plan-eng-review preamble, hooks/agent-result-validator.ts, reviewer anti-skip clauses.
schemaVersion: 1
regressions[3]{id,title,description,detectedDate,sourceIncident,antiPattern,detectionRegex}:
  R-001,direct-edit-bypasses-audit-trail,"Editing a Loom-tracked artifact (ROADMAP.md, PLAN.md, contract-*.md, notes.toon) via direct file writes bypasses the corresponding Loom command's audit side-effects: changelog append, wiki update, state invalidation. This creates 'ghost mutations' that no downstream tooling knows about. Reviewer anti-skip: when reviewing changes to planning/*.md files or protocols/*.md files, verify a corresponding entry exists in planning/history/changelog.md dated same day.",2026-07-01,gstack-adoption dogfood: added F-37 to ROADMAP-gstack-adoption.md via Edit before running /loom-roadmap:mutate,"Loom artifact modified via Write/Edit without corresponding Loom command invocation","(planning/(ROADMAP|plans/PLAN)|protocols/contract-).*\\.(md|toon)"
  R-002,cascading-scope-directives-too-broadly,"When user says 'skip X' (small directive), AI cascades to skip X and everything adjacent to X in the mental hierarchy. Example: 'skip eval stuff' interpreted as 'skip criteria-planner AND plan-review AND verify AND convergence.' Correct pattern: verify scope with one specific example ('so we should skip criteria-plan.toon generation but keep the 6-reviewer plan-review round?') before locking in as a plan-level constraint. Reviewer anti-skip: when a plan has a C-NN constraint sourced from a short user directive, verify the constraint text quotes or references the specific user words that established it.",2026-07-01,gstack-adoption plan-create step: 'i dont care about eval stuff' cascaded to C-03 'no evaluation framework',"C-NN constraint text lacks specific quote/reference to originating user directive","^\\*\\*Decision:\\*\\*.*without.*rationale.*(quote|user said|per operator)"
  R-003,premature-refusal-on-runtime-uncertainty,"When an agent hits an unfamiliar tool availability question, it can bail with 'tool unavailable' without verifying via ToolSearch or a capability probe. Wastes the parent's token budget and produces a false-negative pipeline halt. Correct pattern: probe the runtime (ToolSearch, try/catch on a lightweight invocation) BEFORE claiming tool absence. If truly absent, structured bail with an actionable resumeHint is better than freeform refusal.",2026-07-01,gstack-adoption execute-link first dispatch claimed 'sub-agent spawn tool unavailable' without probing,"Agent returns status:failed with reason='tool X unavailable' without evidence of a capability probe","\"tool.*unavailable\".*(?!ToolSearch|capability probe|try/catch)"
